column3: Sextus Julius Silvanus, son of Sextus
column8: If the reconstruction of Forum Iuli is correct (the monument is now lost), it could refer to Cividale del Friuli (Italia), Fréjus (Gallia Narbonensis), Voghera (Italia)

column3: Lucius Vettius Secundus, son of Marcus

column8: Unsure if Augusta Praetoria (Italia) or Augusta Troas (Asia Minor). Tončinić 2011, 204-205; Fadić 1995 168: Troas may be more likely, as Sergia is a common tribe for Asia Minor citizens, and another Member (Gaius Curiatius) does list Augusta Troas as his place of origin (MonumentID 32, CIL 3, 2019).
